did.unittitle: Irish Broadside Ballads

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: BPP 1001, Department of Rare Books & Special Collections, Hesburgh Libraries of Notre Dame.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Collection consists of 559 broadsides, most measuring 28 x 11 1/2 cm. Broadsides were printed and sold in streets and at fairs and markets from the early days of printing, often by ballad singers. Many of the broadsides were printed in Dublin by P. Brereton, probably between 1860 and 1876.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: There are no access restrictions on this collection.
